review.reviewBody:
@i8thecat

I know it's always a great emotional tragedy when someone on the internet doesn't conform to your personal beliefs, but I'm sure you'll find a way to reconcile with the fact that some cooks enjoy using MSG in their cooking with no adverse side effects. That's probably because of the fact that MSG sensitivity has found to be largely unsubstantiated and psychosomatic.

Also, on a lighter note, I tried this today and was really happy with the results. The seasoning did seem a bit off, it seemed spicier than Chic Fil A sandwiches (I hate spicy things) and so I'll probably still be tinkering with it. However, the important part--the composition and texture of the sandwich itself--was totally perfect. Awesome! I've tried dozens of copycat recipes and none have even come close to these results.
